DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       HHttaaggss makes hypertext of  C,  C++,  Yacc,  Java,  PHP  and
       Assembly source code.

       In  advance  of  using  this  command,  you  must  execute
       ggttaaggss(1) from the root directory of the source tree.  Then
       you can execute hhttaaggss from the same place.  HHttaaggss makes an
       directory named 'HTML' and generates hypertext in it.  You
       can start browsing from 'HTML/index.html'.

       Since  hhttaaggss  generates static hypertext as long as the --DD
       or --ff option is not specified, you can  move  it  anywhere
       and browse it with any browser without web server.

       You  must use same parser for both ggttaaggss(1) and hhttaaggss.  If
       you use the default parser, it is not  necessary  to  con-
       sider for it.


